<HR><H2>[COLD] 'configure' bug in 1.0p24 on linux systems</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Wed Feb 12 00:57:02 1997
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Tue, 11 Feb 1997 22:46:17 -0700 (MST)
From: Brandon Gillespie &lt;brandon@cold.org&gt;
To: coldstuff@cold.org

The new system guessing scripts I grabbed from autoconf changed their
format, but only for linux systems.  This will cause the CPU to report as
'i386-pc' which will cause problems.  If you are on a linux system, you
can solve this problem by trimming '-pc' off any occurance of it.  I will
have it fixed in p25, and in any newer downloads of p24 (its a minor
problem, and not worth a full release imho).

-Brandon

</PRE>
